The classroom seminars provide an overview of the tools and methods related to the creation of a website. Practical work is carried out.
Topics include:
1. Creating a source task and planning a website.
2. Tools and strategy for internet marketing.
3. WordPress content management system.
4. Webpage content creation.
5. Search Engine Optimization.
6. Web analytics.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of this course is to give basic knowledge and skills about internet marketing strategies, creating and managing websites with Wordpress, web analytics and optimising for search engines.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon the completion of the course the student: 1) knows how to create a web page source task; 2) knows the tools of online marketing; 3) knows the possibilities of the free content management system WordPress; 4) knows the role of search engine optimization; 5) knows the possibilities of web analytics; 6) can create a web page source task and an internet marketing strategy; 7) can create a simpler web page with the necessary attachments (web page content creation); 8) can create website content creation; 9) can optimize the web page for search engine; 10) can use Google Analytics' key tools for web analytics.
